, 1978 Fig. 68.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:32382" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Myrmica hirsuta Elmes" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">Myrmica hirsuta Elmes</taxonomicName>
, 1978:131.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="51">
Queen. Similar to a microgyne 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:32436" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" genus.bestMatchDistance="1574" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Myrmica sabuleti Meinert" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabuleti">M. sabuleti</taxonomicName>
but distinguished by the laterally enlarged postpetiole, wider frons and excessive development of body hairs. Head width: 1.05 mm. Body length: 5.2 mm. Mean postpetiole width: 0.675 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="51">
Male. Similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:32436" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" genus.bestMatchDistance="1531" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Myrmica sabuleti Meinert" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabuleti">M. sabuleti</taxonomicName>
except in smaller size and more profuse body hairs. Length: 5.3 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="51">Distribution. Rare, Dorset, South England only.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="51">
Biology. This species was discovered by Elmes (1978) in a small group of colonies containing apparently normal 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:32436" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" genus.bestMatchDistance="1483" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Myrmica sabuleti Meinert" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabuleti">M. sabuleti</taxonomicName>
workers and in some cases normal queens. The small queens were at first assumed to be microgynes of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:32436" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" genus.bestMatchDistance="1461" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Myrmica sabuleti Meinert" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabuleti">M. sabuleti</taxonomicName>
but body pilosity and relative postpetiole measurements were found to be outside the range of that species. In size and appearance 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:32382" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" genus.bestMatchDistance="456" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Myrmica hirsuta Elmes" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsuta">M. hirsuta</taxonomicName>
resembles M. myrmecoxena Forel found once only as a parasite of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:32405" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" genus.bestMatchDistance="24" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Myrmica lobicornis Nylander" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobicornis">M. lobicornis</taxonomicName>
in Switzerland and also has affinities with the similar but much larger 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:32351" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Myrmica bibikoffi Kutter" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bibikoffi">Myrmica bibikoffi Kutter</taxonomicName>
(1963).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
